name: src/charts/barchart.js
Barchart
description:
Barchart implementation. This charts belongs to 'Basic' family.
It is inherited on 'Basic'.

name: constructor
description:
Barchart constructor. It needs (at least) one argument to start: data.
Optionally, you can indicate a second argument that includes all the chart options. If you 
do not specify this, '_default' object is used by default.

name: draw
description: Renders a data object on the chart.

params.name: data
params.description:
This object contains the data that will be rendered on chart. If you do not
specify this param, this.data will be used instead.

name: keepDrawing
description: Add new data to the current graph. If it is empty, this creates a new one.

name: src/charts/base/Chart.js
Chart
description: Base class, which includes common methods for all the charts

name: constructor
description: Non-instanciable Chart. This is the parent class for all the ones (Linechart, Barchart, etc.)

params.name: d

name: _initializeAPI
description: Private method. Initialize the API by dinamically creating methods. It creates N method, one per configuration option

params.name: properties
params.description: An array that contains the name of the methods

name: _getChartContext
description: Return the chart context: data, configuration and type

name: _initializeSVGContext
description:
Initialize the SVG context, by dinamically creating an <svg> tag in the specified selector. It is automatically invoked
by the chart constructor and should not be used outside of this instance.

name: draw
description: Paint data into the chart. If no data is specified, it takes by default the last dataset (very useful when repaintng charts )

name: download
description: Make and download an image of the current state of the chart.

name: keepDrawing
description: This method add a data record / array of data into the current data.

name: change
description: Change a configuration property. They all are also available through a method with the same name of the property.

unknown.tagValue: the instance of the current chart

return.description: the instance of the current chart

name: src/datasources/Datasource.js
Datasource
description:
A Datasource is the name given to the connection set up to a data endpoint. This class defines the common methods for the datasources,
such as start() and stop().

name: constructor
description: Creates an instance of Datasource.

name: start
description: Starts the stream of data

name: stop
description: If started, this method stops the stream of data

name: filter
description: Filters the incoming messages. Each data record that do not comply the filter condition will be discarded

name: src/datasources/WebsocketDatasource.js
WebsocketDatasource
description: This datasource set up a connection to a websocket server.

name: constructor

params.name: source
params.description: A websocket endpoint. If invalid, this class will throw an Error.

name: configure
description: Configure a dispatcher for this datasource.

params.name: dispatcher
params.description: A d3 dispatcher. This dispatcher is in charge of receiving and sending events.

name: start
description: Initialize a websocket connection

name: stop
description: If started, this method close the websocket connection.

import * as Colors from '../colors';

export const defaults =  {
    selector: '#chart',
    colorScale: Colors.diverging_spectral2(),
    invertColorScale: true,
    minLevel: 0,
    maxLevel: 100,
    minAngle: -90,
    maxAngle: 90,
    ringWidth: 50,
    ringMargin: 20,
    labelInset: 10,
    needleNutRadius: 25,
    needleLenghtRatio: 0.8,
    numericIndicator: true,
    label: 'km/h',
    //margins
    marginTop: 20,
    marginRight: 250,
    marginBottom: 30,
    marginLeft: 50,
    //Width & height
    width: '50%', // %, auto, or numeric
    height: 250,
    ticks: 10, // ticks for y dial.
};
